==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dangleberry
<hw>Dan"gle*ber`ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A dark blue, edible berry with a white bloom, and its shrub
(<spn>Gaylussacia frondosa</spn>) closely allied to the common
huckleberry. The bush is also called <prodby>blue tangle</prodby>, and
is found from New England to Kentucky, and southward.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dangler</ent>⟦br⟧
